    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-19T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-19T11:00:00-05:00" n="538"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4R1/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-19T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 19, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 19—1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. I am in receipt of invitation from Secretary General of League of Nations,
                    dated June 18, to the American Government to participate in a conference in
                    Bangkok, Siam, to open November 9, 1931, to discuss position in regard to
                    chapter II of the Hague Convention<note n="21" xml:id="d538fn21">Signed January
                        23, 1912, <ref target="frus1912#pg_196">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1912, p. 196</ref>.</note> and
                    application of the Geneva Agreement<note n="22" xml:id="d538fn22">Signed
                        February 11, 1925, by the British Empire (with India), China, France, Japan,
                        the Netherlands, Portugal, and Siam; League of Nations Treaty Series, vol.
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">li</hi>, p. 337.</note> on the basis of the report
                    to [<hi rend="italic">of</hi>] the Commission of Inquiry into the Control of
                    Opium Smoking in the Far East.<note n="23" xml:id="d538fn23">League of Nations
                        document C.635.M.254.1930.XI. (Geneva, November, 1930).</note> The United
                    States and China are included in this invitation in accordance with a resolution
                    of the Council adopted May 23 last.<note n="24" xml:id="d538fn24">See League of
                        Nations, <hi rend="italic">Sixty-third Session of the Council:</hi> Minutes
                        of the Sixth Meeting (Council/63rd Session/P. V. 6 (1)), p. 3.</note>
                    Mailing invitation today by pouch.<note n="25" xml:id="d538fn25">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
